<subSubSection id="48D355CA8E0CFF8248A753EAFE0CF9D2" pageId="66" pageNumber="67" type="description">
<paragraph id="007606418E0CFF8248A753EAFE61FA0E" blockId="66.[151,1437,1222,1715]" pageId="66" pageNumber="67">
<emphasis id="32BDDA538E0CFF8248A753EAFE34FB2F" bold="true" box="[151,401,1222,1247]" pageId="66" pageNumber="67">Description of Male.</emphasis>
Fully winged; length 
<quantity id="C731ABA48E0CFF824A9153EAFD58FB2E" box="[673,765,1222,1246]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.6" pageId="66" pageNumber="67" unit="mm" value="1.6">1.6 mm</quantity>
. Head black, except mandible testaceous; antenna brown; mesosoma and metasoma black; legs brown. Antenna filiform; antennal segments in following proportions: 7:5:5:5:5:5:5:5:5:7.5. Head dull, granulated; frontal line complete, very slight; POL = 5; OL = 2.5; OOL = 5; OPL = 4; TL = 4; occipital carina complete. Scutum, scutellum and metanotum shiny, finely punctate, unsculptured among punctures. Notauli incomplete, reaching approximately 0.2 length of scutum. Propodeum reticulate rugose, with strong transverse keel between dorsal and posterior surface; posterior surface with two complete longitudinal keels and median area as rugose as lateral areas. Fore wing hyaline, without dark transverse bands; distal part of stigmal vein shorter than proximal part (2:5). Paramere (
<figureCitation id="98F21AC48E0CFF824B2C52EEFC28FA2A" box="[796,909,1474,1498]" captionStart="PLATE 17" captionStartId="68.[151,233,1880,1903]" captionTargetBox="[180,1401,211,1842]" captionTargetId="figure-120@68.[166,1421,195,1858]" captionTargetPageId="68" captionText="PLATE 17. A, D–F. Male genitalia. B. Pronotum and scutum. C, G. Chelae, holotypes. A. Anteon abatanense, holotype (from Olmi 1991). B. A. achterbergi, female from UAE, dorsal view. C. A. achterbergi (from Olmi 1991). D. A. achterbergi from UAE (from Olmi 2008a). E. A. adebratti, holotype (from Olmi 1993d). F. A. amabile, holotype (from Xu et al. 2006a). G. A. acre (from Olmi 1991). Scale bar 0.11 mm for A, 0.17 mm for C and G, 0.14 mm for D and E, 0.19 mm for F." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5278432" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5278432/files/figure.png" pageId="66" pageNumber="67">Plate 17A</figureCitation>
) much shorter than penis, without distal inner process. Tibial spurs 1/1/2.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="007606418E0CFF8248F75127FE0CF9D2" blockId="66.[151,1437,1222,1715]" box="[199,425,1546,1571]" pageId="66" pageNumber="67">
<emphasis id="32BDDA538E0CFF8248F75127FE80F9D3" bold="true" box="[199,293,1547,1571]" pageId="66" pageNumber="67">Female.</emphasis>
Unknown.
</paragraph>
